Description: Part of a small curved trough or the pseudo-kidney shaped pottery vessel with square rim and rounded base, made of dense Nile silt clay, burnished on the exterior and interior walls but not the interior base.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Qaw el-Kebir, Cemetery area 5800 (el Badari)
Curator's comments: Miscellaneous class MS12 in Brunton and Caton Thomspon 1928.
Bibliographic references: Brunton & Caton-Thompson 1928 / The Badarian Civilisation and Predynastic Remains near Badari (14, 23; pl. xvi. MS12)
Acquisition name: Donated by: British School of Archaeology, Egypt
